TacticToe is a tactic-based prover.

It searches for a proof by repeatedly applying suitable tactics for each goal state that it produces.

SKIPPING RECORDING of the HOL4 standard library:
  1) Download the file ttt_tacdata_kananaskis-14.tar.gz from
     http://grid01.ciirc.cvut.cz/~thibault/
  2) Extract it in $HOME/.cache/tactictoe (or in the directory named by
     HOL4_TACTICTOE_CACHE).  This creates the ttt_tacdata directory.
  3) Optionally download from the same location
     "tnn_for_tactictoe" to a file "path_to_tnn"

RECORDING all ancestor theories with manifest-based cache validation:
  load "tttUnfold"; open tttUnfold;
  load "fooTheory";
  ttt_record (); (* takes about 8 hours for the full standard library *)
  (* tip: use ttt_record_thy "foo" to record/update the "foo" Theory *)

The recorder writes ttt_tacdata/MANIFEST under the TacticToe cache root
($HOME/.cache/tactictoe by default, or HOL4_TACTICTOE_CACHE) with content
hashes for each recorded theory and explicit tactic-data and TacticToe
compatibility versions.
Tactic-data files are stored under ttt_tacdata/data using an identity key
derived from the theory name, Script.sml hash, ancestry version, tactic-data
format version, and TacticToe version. Same-name theories from different
projects therefore do not share data unless this full identity matches; old
flat ttt_tacdata/<theory> files are not used for current manifest-validated
loads. Bump `mlTacticData.format_version` when the on-disk format changes,
and `mlTacticData.tactictoe_version` when recorder, feature, or learning
changes invalidate recorded data.
The cache root can also be changed in ML after loading:
  tttSetup.set_tactictoe_cache_dir "/path/to/tactictoe-cache";
If TacticToe has already loaded tactic data, also clear the in-memory cache:
  tacticToe.clean_ttt_tacdata_cache ();
A theory is re-recorded when its Script.sml hash changes, when an ancestor was
re-recorded in the same topological pass, when the data file hash no longer
matches the manifest, or when either compatibility version changes. It logs
every up-to-date, stale, recorded, skipped, and failed decision.

Useful variants:
  ttt_record_opts [Scope (Theories ["foo"]), DryRun true];
  ttt_record_opts [Scope (Ancestry "foo"), Force true];
  ttt_record_opts [Scope (Ancestry "foo"), Parallel 4];

Recording publishes tactic data and thmdata through atomic renames, and
recording runs use per-theory locks under ttt_tacdata/.locks plus a manifest
lock, so concurrent readers never see a partially-written data file.

WARNING: if fooTheory depends on structures not available in sigobj (or in the
holstate), arrange for the generated structure-open script to see those
custom structures; for example, place a Holmakefile in the TacticToe scratch
open directory with the line:
  INCLUDES = directory-of-the-custom-structures
Otherwise, the tactics and arguments declared in those structures will not be
recorded.

DEFAULT USAGE (after RECORDING or SKIPPING RECORDING):
  load "tacticToe"; open tacticToe;
  ttt ([],``1+1=2``);
  tactictoe ``1+1=2``; (* alternatively *)

USAGE with tree neural network:
  load "tacticToe"; open tacticToe;
  val tnn = mlTreeNeuralNetwork.read_tnn "path_to_tnn";
  load "sum_numTheory"; open sum_numTheory;
  set_timeout 60.0;
  ttt_tnn tnn ([],``!n. 2 * SUM (n+1) I = n * (n+1) ``);

USAGE after failure:
  load "tacticToe"; open tacticToe;
  val tnn = mlTreeNeuralNetwork.read_tnn "path_to_tnn";
  load "sum_numTheory"; open sum_numTheory;
  set_timeout 2.0;
  (* also works with ttt *)
  ttt_tnn tnn ([],``!n. 2 * SUM (n+1) I = n * (n+1) ``);
  suggest_depth := NONE;
  suggest ();

CLEANING:
  TacticToe depends on data stored in the TacticToe cache root
  ($HOME/.cache/tactictoe by default, or HOL4_TACTICTOE_CACHE).
  The manifest-based recorder re-records stale tactic data automatically.
  To force a fresh cache, call tttUnfold.ttt_clean_record ().

EXAMPLE: see examples in src/tactictoe/examples.

NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS:
  Keep up-to-date:
  1) core theories in src/AI/sml_inspection/smlOpen.sml
  2) infix tokens in src/tactictoe/src/tttInfix.sml,
  3) polyml values in src/tactictoe/src/tttUnfold.sml.
  Debugging directories:
  1) Output of the modified theory foo is can be found in
     $HOME/.cache/tactictoe/tmp/<session>/sml_inspection/buildheap/
     buildheap_fooScript_ttt.
     Set aiLib.debug_flag and to true or/and smlRedirect.hide_flag to false
     for more output.
  2) A copy of the modified theory is saved under
     $HOME/.cache/tactictoe/log/scripts
     for further inspection.
